This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with Kettle Moraine Lutheran High School. No contact with any individuals identified in ID Key filed in 22CF514 or their residences. No unsupervised contact with anyone under age 18 except family members. Not possess devices with internet capability without parental supervision and only for school/work or for legal consultation or for counseling. Parental supervision for legal consultation and counseling by zoom shall be reasonable and in recognition of defendant's right to confidentiality in legal consultation and counseling. No direct or indirect contact with M.R.S. or their residence.

Defendant Bryan Otto Seban appeared by video from Washington Co Jail, in custody. Attorney Jonathan A. LaVoy in court for Bryan Otto Seban. Prosecuting attorney Stephanie L Hanson in court for the State of Wisconsin. Def given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found. Preliminary hearing time limits waived. Hearing scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
